			<title>Suicide Squad - With Spoilers - Do not click - You have been warned.</title>
			<link>http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?78903-Suicide-Squad-With-Spoilers-Do-not-click-You-have-been-warned&amp;goto=newpost</link>
			<pubDate>Fri, 05 Aug 2016 14:42:27 GMT</pubDate>
			<description><![CDATA[Loved the movie.  Best DC movie to date (not as awesome of a statement as it should be) 
 
I think they handled almost every single character very well. 
 
If there is a concern its that people who didn't have the exposure to comics wont get some of it, but my lovely lady really enjoyed the movie...]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>Loved the movie.  Best DC movie to date (not as awesome of a statement as it should be)<br />
<br />
I think they handled almost every single character very well.<br />
<br />
If there is a concern its that people who didn't have the exposure to comics wont get some of it, but my lovely lady really enjoyed the movie and she didn't know about any of it.  Her only real comment was I wish there was more Joker.<br />
<br />
The play between Harley and the Joker seemed to really nail the spirit and fun that I remember from Batman the Animated Series, without making the Joker a joke.  He did a superb job, very different than Heath, but he really felt like the Joker to me.<br />
<br />
Amanda Waller hit me like she did in the original run of of the comics.  Almost as Evil (if not more so) than the bad guys and tough enough to have a screaming argument with Batman.  She made a few mistakes that would be out of character for an experienced waller, but seemed legit for a person getting used to the idea of meta humans and how to deal with them.<br />
<br />
I really liked Captain Boomerang.  This may be the first movie where I thoroughly enjoyed that actor.  If any complaints pop up, its that he didn't get enough lines, but that can be said about everyone but 3 people.  Capt B suckering Slipnot into running for it made me happy.  I knew Slipnot wasn't long for the world just from the previews and honestly because he was slipnot.  I even expected him to be the &quot;we aren't bluffing guy&quot; but I was glad they let boomerang talk him into it.<br />
<br />
Killer Croc.  Wanted more of him, but seemed a good fit.  Wish he was bigger, but to do him like I'd probably want it would have been CGI and this probably made it better.  Full CGI characters are still a bit hard for me to &quot;believe&quot;  Honestly I've been a fan of Adebesi since OZ.<br />
<br />
Deadshot.  Technically a bad guy, but they used the Anti-hero version of him.  Its shocking they gave Will the starring role I know, but it was handled very well.  Maybe he was a bit too nice, but he was obviously the one that was center stage for showing that he was a Bad Guy vs an Evil Guy.  I highly suspect he will show up in some other movies as bit parts and future Suicide Sqauds will probably run like they did in the comics with him taking the role of Rick.<br />
<br />
Harley.  Awesome.  Again... very much the feel of Harley from the Animated show.  When she called him Mr. J the teenage boy in me was so happy.  It wasn't even a special event, just casually throwing it in.<br />
<br />
Rick Flagg.  Well, he was Rick Flagg.  He did what he was supposed to do.  He shines like he did in the comics.  Which in my opinion was a place holder until Deadshot takes over.<br />
<br />
Enchantress. I liked the dirtyish costume more than the ancient queenish looking costume.  Seemed a good version of what I remember, but she never really stood out from my comic book days.<br />
<br />
Diablo.  Really liked how he was handled the whole way through.  I liked him so much I was sad when he died.  I would hope they could figure out a way to bring him back, but probably not a good idea really.<br />
<br />
Batman was ok.  I liked the exchange between Bruce and Amanda at the end and it was the best use of him in the show.  I can't be disappointed in the other parts too much because it was more of a Stan Lee pop in , than a role.<br />
<br />
They blended the music into the movie really well.  And unless Harley had an ipod with a Joker mix that she could play I don't think they could have tied it more directly in, but the musical choices where very good.<br />
<br />
<br />
Plot.  Notice how I havent talked about it much...  Well With all those characters there isnt a ton of room.  Basically Go get person X out of hell city or we blow off your head.  Hey this didnt work out like we thought.  Guess we have to actually STOP the EVIL (not BAD) guy or else we get blamed.  Yay we win!  This was very much a vehicle to get this many people in the movie, get them to say stuff we want to hear, and have a fun bad guy road trip movie.<br />
<br />
I hope everyone likes it as much as me.</div>

]]></content:encoded>
