			<link>http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?78902-root-canals-suck&amp;goto=newpost</link>
			<pubDate>Fri, 05 Aug 2016 01:41:54 GMT</pubDate>
			<description>For the past year, chewing and cold have caused a fuckton of pain on my lower left molar.  My dentist thought it was a receding gum line and that my root was hypersensitive.  He tried a few surface fillings on the tooth to stop the pain (with no luck).  So he finally recommended a root canal -...</description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>For the past year, chewing and cold have caused a fuckton of pain on my lower left molar.  My dentist thought it was a receding gum line and that my root was hypersensitive.  He tried a few surface fillings on the tooth to stop the pain (with no luck).  So he finally recommended a root canal - which is good since it turns out the tooth is cracked and has been for over a year.<br />
<br />
Now, the root canal SUCKED.  It was not the pain, it was the inability to breath with my head tilted that far back and my mouth wide open.  Rubber dam also did not help.  Could not breath through my mouth and I could feel my tongue blocking part of my airway (shocking considering I have sleep apnea).  60 minutes sitting in the chair with the Dr's hands and tools in my mouth with a bite block to keep my mouth open and feeling like I could only get 25% of the air I needed - GOOD TIMES....<br />
<br />
Then about 40 minutes in my left shoulder started to ache severely.  Something about sitting back in a chair that is not wide enough to support your shoulders.  Yeah, good times...<br />
<br />
All that being said, the actual root canal portion was relatively painless.  All the other crap made me wish I had asked for the tooth to be pulled</div>

